1
00:00:05,464 --> 00:00:11,886
- [footsteps]
- [River grunts, retches] [Jackson] Oh, for fuck's sake, Cartwright. Not now.

2
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:13,471
Here, give me your phone.

3
00:00:13,472 --> 00:00:15,056
- [River] Huh?
- Give me your phone!

4
00:00:15,057 --> 00:00:16,177
- Phone.
- [Louisa] For what?

5
00:00:16,225 --> 00:00:17,809
Just give me your phone.

6
00:00:17,893 --> 00:00:19,853
- [River breathing heavily]
- Where's Harper?

7
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:22,939
- What the fuck? Who's th...
- Hey. Phone.

8
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:23,982
- My phone?
- Your phone!

9
00:00:24,066 --> 00:00:25,650
Fuck off. I FaceTime my kids on this.

10
00:00:25,651 --> 00:00:28,486
I don't care if you ArseTime
the Pope on it. Give it to me.

11
00:00:28,487 --> 00:00:30,530
Service phones have tracking enabled.

12
00:00:30,531 --> 00:00:35,493
- We need to disappear.
- [splashing] Now, you three, go fetch Ho and Loy.

13
00:00:35,494 --> 00:00:38,037
And you better move it unless you want
the Dogs to bite your cocks off.

14
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,915
Yeah, hold...
We don't know where they live.

15
00:00:40,499 --> 00:00:42,625
423 Middlesex Court, Hackney.

16
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:44,669
16 Mervan Road, Brixton.

17
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:47,380
You can figure out
the fucking postcodes yourselves.

18
00:00:47,381 --> 00:00:48,966
- Then where?
- You know where.

19
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:50,925
Where?

20
00:00:50,926 --> 00:00:52,177
Blake's grave. [sighs]

21
00:00:52,845 --> 00:00:54,555
- [River spits]
- [Min] W-Wait, where?

22
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,182
[River grunts, sniffles]

23
00:00:57,266 --> 00:00:59,934
[sighs] I've definitely seen him before.
I recognized him.

24
00:00:59,935 --> 00:01:02,020
- Who?
- [sighs] The head.

25
00:01:03,564 --> 00:01:05,065
He's one of us. [sighs]

26
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:06,733
Was one of us.

27
00:02:17,554 --> 00:02:21,558
What did you do?
What the fuck just happened?

28
00:02:22,142 --> 00:02:23,352
He was a traitor.

29
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,187
A spook.

30
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:28,190
I spoke to Simmonds.

31
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:31,609
When?

32
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:34,112
[Curly] I had a prepaid. Can't be traced.

33
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:40,034
Look, if I hadn't dealt with that scum, we'd still be sitting there waiting for the cops to show up.

34
00:02:40,035 --> 00:02:41,119
Or the SAS.

35
00:02:41,203 --> 00:02:43,080
And those bastards shoot to kill.

36
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,415
What I did was self-defense.

37
00:02:45,499 --> 00:02:47,876
Self-defense? He was unarmed.

38
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,355
- [Curly] He'd have done the same to us.
- The same to us how?

39
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:52,130
He'd have slung us in jail, that's how!

40
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:53,882
How long do you think we'd last in there?

41
00:02:53,966 --> 00:02:56,426
Bleeding out in the corner
from some terrorist shank.

42
00:02:56,510 --> 00:03:01,932
- I ain't going out like that.
- No, mate. That doesn't make any sense because he organized it, didn't he?

43
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:03,517
Remember?

44
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:06,561
He came to us, yeah?

45
00:03:06,562 --> 00:03:08,646
And then we all took the plan to Simmonds.

46
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:10,065
He set us up!

47
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:13,443
- Nah.
- [Curly] He was too keen, too hard-line.

48
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:14,861
He'd never have gone through with it.

49
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:17,614
[grunts]
We weren't supposed to see it through.

50
00:03:17,698 --> 00:03:19,157
No one was supposed to die.

51
00:03:19,241 --> 00:03:20,700
- That was the point.
- What are we gonna do?

52
00:03:20,701 --> 00:03:23,661
He's playing cards,
and you cut his fucking head off!

53
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:26,080
- What the fuck are we gonna fucking do?
- Whoa, whoa. Take it easy!

54
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:32,128
- Shh. Take it easy. I say, I say...
- [groans] - Listen. We let the kid go. - [breathing heavily] - He can identify us. - No, no, no.

55
00:03:32,129 --> 00:03:33,546
He's been hooded up.

56
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:35,715
[stammers] He's caught a glimpse at best.

57
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:37,675
He's heard our voices.
He's listening to you right now.

58
00:03:37,676 --> 00:03:40,553
[Zeppo chuckles] So... So what? So what?

59
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,055
He doesn't know our names, yeah?

60
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:44,140
[Curly] Danny Campbell, 14 Dunlop Terrace.

61
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:45,475
Hey! La, la, la, la, la. Hey!

62
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:48,061
What are you fucking playing at, hey?

63
00:03:48,896 --> 00:03:51,272
Hey, kid, did you hear that?
Did you hear that?

64
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:53,399
He's getting a good look
at your face right now.

65
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,569
Fuck you. Fuck you.

66
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:58,822
- Kid, did you hear that?
- Mm-mmm.

67
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,657
If he didn't, I can say it again louder.

68
00:04:00,741 --> 00:04:02,784
You are a fucking snake, do you know that?

69
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,327
- I suggest you shut your mouth...
- You fucking...

70
00:04:04,328 --> 00:04:08,081
- or I'll say your name and all.
- [panting] [chuckles] Yeah.

71
00:04:08,165 --> 00:04:10,041
[breathing heavily]

72
00:04:10,042 --> 00:04:11,126
Yeah.

73
00:04:11,627 --> 00:04:13,587
[news anchor speaking on TV, indistinct]

74
00:04:17,007 --> 00:04:25,265
[news anchor 2] There's been no indication
from the security services to suggest they are any closer to discovering the whereabouts of the kidnapped student, Hassan Ahmed.

75
00:04:25,349 --> 00:04:32,730
And while many are hoping
for his safe return, there are still millions across the world who are continuing to share the hostage video.

76
00:04:32,731 --> 00:04:33,815
To explore the situation...

77
00:04:33,899 --> 00:04:35,275
[cell phone buzzes]

78
00:04:35,359 --> 00:04:36,235
Yes?

79
00:04:36,236 --> 00:04:38,403
We confirmed the victim. It's Alan Black.

80
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:41,739
Hassan?

81
00:04:42,491 --> 00:04:43,741
No trace.

82
00:04:43,742 --> 00:04:46,620
[sniffs] Black died about 20 minutes ago.

83
00:04:47,955 --> 00:04:48,956
Lamb?

84
00:04:49,498 --> 00:04:51,708
Gone. His car's here.
We're bringing it in.

85
00:04:51,792 --> 00:04:54,335
The back door's been forced,
so it looks like he wasn't alone.

86
00:04:54,336 --> 00:04:56,713
Neighbor opposite said
she saw a group in a huddle.

87
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,214
Slow Horses.

88
00:04:58,215 --> 00:05:01,092
- [knocks]
- [door unlocks, opens] Whatever it is can wait.

89
00:05:01,093 --> 00:05:03,387
[Singh]
First Desk is on the secure line, ma'am.

90
00:05:03,971 --> 00:05:05,138
Uh, I was told it was urgent.

91
00:05:07,391 --> 00:05:08,392
I have to go.

92
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,019
Secure the scene. Deep clean.

93
00:05:11,645 --> 00:05:13,021
Get here as fast as you can.

94
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:23,323
[phone rings]

95
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:25,950
Ingrid.

96
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:28,870
Let me reassure you, there is no need
to distract from your trip.

97
00:05:28,871 --> 00:05:32,290
I'm already at the airport, having walked
out of a State Department meeting.

98
00:05:32,291 --> 00:05:35,001
Have you completely lost control
over there? What's going on?

99
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:37,087
- Lamb's gone AWOL.
- Christ.

100
00:05:37,171 --> 00:05:39,816
[Diana] I've been worried about him,
which is why I put Sid Baker in there.

101
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,633
What's Baker saying about Alan Black?

102
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:44,720
She's in hospital.

103
00:05:46,013 --> 00:05:48,682
She took a bullet
in a detail with Cartwright Jr.

104
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,601
Right.

105
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:54,729
I want Lamb and his rejects
off the street and into the Park.

106
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:57,565
I need to know exactly our level
of exposure here.

107
00:05:57,566 --> 00:05:58,650
Where's the boy?

108
00:05:58,734 --> 00:06:00,110
I've pulled everyone in.

109
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:03,363
SO15 are standing by,
and command center is aware.

110
00:06:03,447 --> 00:06:06,157
Clean this up by the time I land.

111
00:06:06,158 --> 00:06:09,703
And if it is the Slow Horses behind it,
bury them.

112
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,292
[sighs]

113
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:20,297
Fuck.

114
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:27,721
[sirens wailing]

115
00:06:40,359 --> 00:06:41,519
[Jackson] Twenty for the hat.

116
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:43,987
Cheers.

117
00:06:55,374 --> 00:06:57,751
["The Scientist" playing on car stereo]

118
00:06:59,837 --> 00:07:02,130
- [stereo button clicks]
- [song continues]

119
00:07:02,214 --> 00:07:04,299
[button clicking]

120
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:06,134
Min, is there no way to turn that off?

121
00:07:06,218 --> 00:07:10,513
Uh, no. Uh, the CD's jammed in and... and the stereo doesn't turn off.

122
00:07:10,514 --> 00:07:11,931
Can you at least change the song?

123
00:07:11,932 --> 00:07:13,933
It's stuck.
It doesn't turn off. That's the issue.

124
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:15,727
- Oh, my God.
- Fuck me, who cares?

125
00:07:15,811 --> 00:07:18,438
Look, what do we know about Alan Black?

126
00:07:18,522 --> 00:07:19,731
Uh... [sighs]

127
00:07:19,815 --> 00:07:23,276
I know that he left Slough House
about a year ago, way before you joined.

128
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:25,111
- Uh-huh.
- Where do you know him from?

129
00:07:25,112 --> 00:07:26,446
I t... [sighs]

130
00:07:26,530 --> 00:07:28,948
- Maybe the Park.
- He was kicked out of the Park years ago.

131
00:07:28,949 --> 00:07:31,702
Yeah, for sleeping with the wife
of the Venezuelan ambassador.

132
00:07:32,494 --> 00:07:34,204
How did Lamb know to go to that house?

133
00:07:34,288 --> 00:07:36,539
Taverner, must be. He met her earlier.

134
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:39,292
- What is this? Lamb and Taverner?
- Fucking hell.

135
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,376
Lamb's cut us loose.

136
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:42,522
That envelope he took off Moody,
that was his flight fund.

137
00:07:42,546 --> 00:07:44,214
If he wanted to, he could just disappear.

138
00:07:44,298 --> 00:07:47,884
Oh, fucking hell, we are fucked.
Fuck, we really are fucked.

139
00:07:47,885 --> 00:07:49,636
Yeah, yeah, but I don't think he will.

140
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,887
[inhales sharply, clicks tongue]

141
00:07:50,888 --> 00:07:53,431
He broke me out when I was being guarded
by that Dog. He didn't have to.

142
00:07:53,432 --> 00:07:55,183
No, no, that's... that's different.

143
00:07:55,184 --> 00:07:57,227
No, look. Lamb will have a play.

144
00:07:57,936 --> 00:07:59,020
He doesn't like to lose.

145
00:07:59,021 --> 00:08:00,355
Okay, so what do we do?

146
00:08:01,064 --> 00:08:02,190
Do we do what Lamb said?

147
00:08:02,191 --> 00:08:06,194
Or do we head to Regent's Park
and... and turn ourselves in?

148
00:08:06,195 --> 00:08:08,322
- Stick to Lamb's plan.
- Turn ourselves in.

149
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:10,490
Right. Fine.

150
00:08:10,574 --> 00:08:17,580
I say that we round up everybody, head to Blake's grave, and if Lamb doesn't show, then we know he's fucked us.

151
00:08:17,581 --> 00:08:19,208
- Yeah.
- Yes, stick to the plan.

152
00:08:20,792 --> 00:08:22,961
Oh, shit, did either of you get
Ho or Loy's addresses?

153
00:08:23,045 --> 00:08:26,756
Uh-huh. Yes. It was... [sniffs, sighs]

154
00:08:26,757 --> 00:08:30,135
- It was a crescent.
- 423 Middlesex Court, Hackney, E9.

155
00:08:30,219 --> 00:08:32,596
16 Mervan Road, Brixton, SW2.

156
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:35,515
God, and postcodes.

157
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:38,352
- Bagsy, not get Ho.
- Yeah, nor me.

158
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,270
Fucking... Thank you.

159
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:45,108
Right, you two get Struan. I'll get Ho.

160
00:09:19,434 --> 00:09:21,270
[engine starts]

161
00:09:42,332 --> 00:09:43,333
[grunts]

162
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:45,419
[typing]

163
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:51,466
- [card reader beeps]
- [door opens] [Nick] Ma'am.

164
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:52,592
Where's the boy?

165
00:09:52,593 --> 00:09:54,761
[Nick sighs]
We're tracking multiple vehicles.

166
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:56,471
What does "multiple" mean?

167
00:09:56,555 --> 00:10:00,934
Thirty-five vehicles passed
the traffic cams at the end of Roupell Street 15 minutes before Lamb went in.

168
00:10:01,018 --> 00:10:02,811
[breathes deeply, stammers]

169
00:10:02,895 --> 00:10:05,271
Ma'am, I know it's not my place
to ask, but what is going on?

170
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:07,191
You're right. It's not your place.

171
00:10:14,198 --> 00:10:15,657
Why do you think Lamb bolted?

172
00:10:17,326 --> 00:10:19,554
Maybe he saw Black's head
and worried about what it looked like.

173
00:10:19,578 --> 00:10:20,995
It looked like what it was.

174
00:10:20,996 --> 00:10:24,624
The head of the Slow Horse is panicking
because a Slow Horse op went south.

175
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:28,044
Lamb's gone rogue,
and one of my agents is dead.

176
00:10:28,045 --> 00:10:29,379
[sighs] Jesus Christ.

177
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:31,589
[stammers] Who knows about this?

178
00:10:31,590 --> 00:10:34,635
You, me, First Desk,
and it stays that way.

179
00:10:35,302 --> 00:10:36,511
I'll keep the Hub on Hassan.

180
00:10:36,512 --> 00:10:38,430
And I want you and your Dogs
on the Slow Horses.

181
00:10:38,514 --> 00:10:40,306
I'll bring Lamb in myself.

182
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:42,434
This is an alias he's likely to use.

183
00:10:43,018 --> 00:10:44,853
If he surfaces, take backup.

184
00:10:46,188 --> 00:10:47,939
Oh, and, Duffy?

185
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:50,608
If anyone gets hurt,
I'd rather it were Lamb.

186
00:10:50,609 --> 00:10:53,695
I can be sure of your silence.
I won't lose any sleep over his.

187
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:06,500
- [Larry] Where the fuck are we going?
- [Curly] Out of London.

188
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,794
- By the backstreets. No cameras.
- Then what?

189
00:11:09,795 --> 00:11:11,505
Why did you tell him my name?

190
00:11:13,257 --> 00:11:14,341
To focus you.

191
00:11:15,676 --> 00:11:17,427
There's only one way out of this.

192
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:22,640
- What, the boat?
- What?

193
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:24,017
[chuckles]

194
00:11:24,101 --> 00:11:26,102
My cousin's boat in Harwich.

195
00:11:26,103 --> 00:11:28,855
- That was the backup plan.
- [Larry] You and that fucking boat.

196
00:11:28,856 --> 00:11:33,651
[Zeppo] No, no, no, listen.
If it gets us to Holland or France, - whichever is close... - I'm not getting on a boat, mate.

197
00:11:33,652 --> 00:11:34,903
I've got a little girl.

198
00:11:35,404 --> 00:11:37,614
Hey, you never see your daughter.

199
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,950
Do you? [chuckles]

200
00:11:41,785 --> 00:11:43,328
Is that what Simmonds said?

201
00:11:43,412 --> 00:11:45,914
"Get to the boat," yeah?
"Get to the boat."

202
00:11:45,998 --> 00:11:47,207
- Simmonds?
- Yeah?

203
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,085
Nah, he wanted us to walk out,
take no action.

204
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:54,006
- [Zeppo] What?
- Fuck off.

205
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:56,800
- Christ.
- No.

206
00:11:58,468 --> 00:12:00,179
We're on our own, aren't we?

207
00:12:02,097 --> 00:12:03,640
- Aren't we?
- We don't need him.

208
00:12:04,266 --> 00:12:06,309
Simmonds could've got us money.

209
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:10,021
- He could've got us new IDs.
- [laughs] - Got us out of this! - [Curly] We don't need Simmonds!

210
00:12:10,022 --> 00:12:11,856
[Larry]
What you did back there, that was you.

211
00:12:11,857 --> 00:12:14,067
- It was you!
- [Curly] Do you think the cops will care?

212
00:12:14,151 --> 00:12:15,360
You still kidnapped someone.

213
00:12:15,444 --> 00:12:16,986
- You still threatened to kill him.
- [Larry] Yeah.

214
00:12:16,987 --> 00:12:19,549
- [Curly] Just listen to me.
- [Larry] We didn't mean that, did we?

215
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,551
- [Curly] Oh! You didn't mean it?
- No, we didn't mean it!

216
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:23,576
- No, we were gonna let him go, weren't we?
- Yeah.

217
00:12:23,577 --> 00:12:25,453
[Larry]
How long would that have got us inside?

218
00:12:25,454 --> 00:12:27,289
Like, two years.

219
00:12:28,373 --> 00:12:30,417
I could do that, mate.
I've done it before...

220
00:12:30,501 --> 00:12:33,211
Listen, listen, I say we stop the van now.

221
00:12:33,212 --> 00:12:35,130
We let the kid go, yeah?

222
00:12:35,839 --> 00:12:37,173
And we get out of the country.

223
00:12:37,174 --> 00:12:39,051
You just told him the escape route.

224
00:12:39,843 --> 00:12:41,136
No, no, no.

225
00:12:41,220 --> 00:12:43,472
We tie him up in the woods
somewhere on the way.

226
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:47,016
We'll be gone by the time they find him.

227
00:12:47,017 --> 00:12:48,185
We'll be gone.

228
00:12:50,312 --> 00:12:51,396
Yeah?

229
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:54,065
Yes?

230
00:12:54,066 --> 00:12:55,400
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

231
00:12:57,027 --> 00:12:58,487
Yeah, yeah, all right. The boat.

232
00:12:59,029 --> 00:13:00,030
Yeah.

233
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,890
- [door opens]
- [whispering] Whoa, whoa. Wait.

234
00:13:25,764 --> 00:13:26,849
Give Daddy a big hug.

235
00:13:29,268 --> 00:13:32,437
All right, monkeys, let Daddy go.
He's got important business.

236
00:13:32,521 --> 00:13:35,482
- At the Park?
- At the Park, yes. It's hush-hush.

237
00:13:36,859 --> 00:13:38,277
Isn't that right, Agent Pierce?

238
00:13:39,653 --> 00:13:41,321
[sighs] Quite so.

239
00:13:41,405 --> 00:13:43,073
Shall we, Agent Loy?

240
00:13:47,536 --> 00:13:49,162
[grunts, groans]

241
00:13:50,163 --> 00:13:51,707
[car doors close]

242
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:05,762
Hey, we should keep kissing 'cause
they might see us in the rearview mirror.

243
00:14:07,306 --> 00:14:08,849
[sighs] Well, let me drive.

244
00:14:14,938 --> 00:14:16,690
Where are you? Where are you?

245
00:14:19,776 --> 00:14:21,778
[dubstep playing, indistinct]

246
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:25,782
[music continues, louder]

247
00:14:35,918 --> 00:14:38,295
[dubstep continues, muffled]

248
00:14:54,895 --> 00:14:57,314
[dubstep blaring through wall]

249
00:15:06,782 --> 00:15:08,033
[doorbell buzzing]

250
00:15:08,951 --> 00:15:11,370
[dubstep playing loudly]

251
00:15:12,579 --> 00:15:13,914
[doorbell buzzes]

252
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:16,500
[doorbell buzzes]

253
00:15:23,507 --> 00:15:24,508
[doorbell buzzes]

254
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:36,937
- [keys jingle]
- [lock clicks] - What's happenin', bruv? - I'm looking for Ho.

255
00:15:37,521 --> 00:15:38,814
No Ho here, man.

256
00:15:39,314 --> 00:15:40,315
[grunts]

257
00:15:41,024 --> 00:15:42,275
Why the fuck are you here?

258
00:15:42,276 --> 00:15:45,403
[breathing heavily] There's been a
complaint about your music. It's shit.

259
00:15:45,404 --> 00:15:46,488
Come on. We gotta go.

260
00:15:47,573 --> 00:15:48,782
Come on!

261
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:51,994
- [horn honking]
- [tires squealing]

262
00:15:53,954 --> 00:15:55,330
[tires screech]

263
00:15:58,667 --> 00:15:59,793
[Nick] Are you in charge?

264
00:15:59,877 --> 00:16:02,129
Show us your CCTV footage
from 20 minutes ago.

265
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:08,051
["The Scientist" playing on stereo]

266
00:16:08,135 --> 00:16:09,511
[Min] Um, so.

267
00:16:09,595 --> 00:16:11,846
Do you w-want to talk about
what just happened?

268
00:16:11,847 --> 00:16:14,224
Well, we were too late is what happened.

269
00:16:14,308 --> 00:16:15,809
No. I... I... I meant us.

270
00:16:16,852 --> 00:16:20,272
I think we should talk about
how we evade MI5 security, Min.

271
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:23,149
Well, it turns out
we evade them by kissing.

272
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:27,779
There's not gonna be any "us"
if we don't stay ahead of the Dogs and work out what the fuck Black was up to.

273
00:16:27,863 --> 00:16:31,074
Yes, of course.
But once, um... once that's sorted...

274
00:16:32,117 --> 00:16:33,868
[stammers] ..."us" could still be a thing?

275
00:16:33,869 --> 00:16:36,038
Less likely every time you bring it up.

276
00:16:42,419 --> 00:16:43,462
Hey, come on.

277
00:16:45,797 --> 00:16:47,382
They might let us share a cell.

278
00:16:48,509 --> 00:16:51,053
[chuckles, sighs]

279
00:16:52,095 --> 00:16:57,226
- God. We really, really are fucked.
- [sighs] [cashier] There.

280
00:16:58,602 --> 00:16:59,770
Yeah, that's him.

281
00:17:03,565 --> 00:17:04,775
Out.

282
00:17:05,442 --> 00:17:07,861
Now. Three. Two.

283
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:10,656
[Webb inhales sharply]

284
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:15,618
[Webb] Yeah, here we go.

285
00:17:17,371 --> 00:17:20,499
[cell phone buzzing]

286
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,002
- Duffy.
- [Nick] He's using that ID you gave me.

287
00:17:24,086 --> 00:17:25,878
Booked a 06:00 a.m. flight to Istanbul.

288
00:17:26,463 --> 00:17:28,757
- Are you sure?
- I'm looking at the CCTV right now.

289
00:17:28,841 --> 00:17:31,093
His face is obscured, but it's Lamb.

290
00:17:32,469 --> 00:17:34,388
- We're off to Gatwick.
- [Webb] Duffy!

291
00:17:35,180 --> 00:17:36,181
Hold on.

292
00:17:38,183 --> 00:17:40,310
[sighs] Look at this.

293
00:17:41,979 --> 00:17:44,147
Oh, you dirty bastard.

294
00:17:44,231 --> 00:17:45,231
What?

295
00:17:45,232 --> 00:17:51,988
He's also booked flights from Heathrow,
Stansted, London City, Birmingham, and Manchester. He knows we'll have to cover 'em all.

296
00:17:51,989 --> 00:17:54,783
- [Diana] He's drawing us off.
- Yeah, while he runs for a ferry.

297
00:17:54,867 --> 00:17:57,035
No. I know where he's going.

298
00:17:57,119 --> 00:18:01,790
- [banging on door]
- [gasps, breathing heavily] [whispers] Oh, God.

299
00:18:02,749 --> 00:18:04,126
[banging]

300
00:18:13,343 --> 00:18:15,053
[banging]

301
00:18:17,472 --> 00:18:18,807
[banging]

302
00:18:23,645 --> 00:18:26,440
Whoever you are, back off. I'm armed.

303
00:18:27,441 --> 00:18:29,526
- [Jackson] No, you're not.
- Lamb?

304
00:18:30,319 --> 00:18:32,237
- [sighs]
- [Jackson] Come on. Open up.

305
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:43,790
- Now.
- [dead bolts sliding] It... It's the middle of the night.

306
00:18:43,874 --> 00:18:45,959
You can't just show up unannounced.

307
00:18:46,043 --> 00:18:47,836
No. Leave the light off.

308
00:18:50,255 --> 00:18:51,465
What do you want?

309
00:18:52,424 --> 00:18:53,883
Fallen off the wagon, have we?

310
00:18:53,884 --> 00:18:56,053
Oh, it's actually a water bottle.

311
00:18:56,553 --> 00:18:58,138
You've probably never seen one.

312
00:18:59,097 --> 00:19:00,098
[Jackson] Get dressed.

313
00:19:01,058 --> 00:19:03,685
- I live here. You can't tell me...
- Just get dressed!

314
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:13,278
Where are we going?

315
00:19:16,073 --> 00:19:17,073
Where are we going?

316
00:19:17,074 --> 00:19:19,200
- What are you doing?
- I'll tell you on the way.

317
00:19:19,201 --> 00:19:21,036
We just gotta move fast.
The Dogs are on us.

318
00:19:21,662 --> 00:19:24,498
Why are they after me?
I've not done anything.

319
00:19:25,415 --> 00:19:27,626
Well, nothing they'd be able to trace.

320
00:19:29,378 --> 00:19:31,004
We gotta keep switching vehicles.

321
00:19:36,718 --> 00:19:40,556
You can't hot-wire any of these.
You need to hack the alarm system.

322
00:19:41,682 --> 00:19:43,322
I can help with that for the right price.

323
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:47,145
- Oh, come on.
- [car doors lock] I'll go analog.

324
00:19:52,734 --> 00:19:55,737
[patron]
I'll have a bacon double cheeseburger...

325
00:19:55,821 --> 00:20:01,535
- [server] Yeah?
- Chips, a can of Fanta and... [sighs]

326
00:20:02,744 --> 00:20:05,104
- You just got Kit Kats and TWIX, yeah?
- Just that, thanks.

327
00:20:05,914 --> 00:20:06,915
[door opens]

328
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,501
[Roddy] Listen.

329
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:17,092
If you're in any kind of personal trouble, I just want you to know I couldn't give a fuck.

330
00:20:17,176 --> 00:20:18,968
And I don't want to be dragged into it.

331
00:20:18,969 --> 00:20:20,261
Yeah, you're already in it.

332
00:20:20,262 --> 00:20:21,555
Wha...

333
00:20:26,185 --> 00:20:32,357
- Fuck! Whoa!
- [tires squealing] Fuck!

334
00:20:32,441 --> 00:20:33,442
[phone rings]

335
00:20:35,027 --> 00:20:36,152
Yeah?

336
00:20:36,153 --> 00:20:38,238
[receptionist]
We have Loy downstairs for you, ma'am.

337
00:20:38,822 --> 00:20:40,073
Oh, I'll be right down.

338
00:21:01,136 --> 00:21:02,804
[elevator door opens]

339
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:06,642
Ma'am.

340
00:21:18,111 --> 00:21:25,202
- [door lock clicks]
- [door opens] Hello.

341
00:21:25,827 --> 00:21:26,828
[sighs]

342
00:21:27,371 --> 00:21:29,873
Would you excuse me a minute?
I just... [groans]

343
00:21:29,957 --> 00:21:33,918
It is relentless up there. [chuckles]

344
00:21:33,919 --> 00:21:36,630
- I can imagine.
- Oh, no, you can't.

345
00:21:37,256 --> 00:21:38,549
None of you can.

346
00:21:41,218 --> 00:21:43,554
How does it feel to be back here
at the Park?

347
00:21:44,513 --> 00:21:47,265
Well, this isn't really
the Park I knew. [chuckles]

348
00:21:47,266 --> 00:21:51,144
I mean, I've never been down here.
I didn't know we had rooms like this.

349
00:21:51,228 --> 00:21:52,604
Not many people do.

350
00:21:53,105 --> 00:21:54,898
That's why I chose it for you.

351
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:57,943
I don't want anyone to know you're here.

352
00:22:01,738 --> 00:22:05,242
Um, m-my wife knows I'm here... [laughs]
at the Park... [stammering]

353
00:22:05,742 --> 00:22:08,036
She still thinks you work here,
doesn't she?

354
00:22:09,705 --> 00:22:11,385
I've been trying to find the right moment.

355
00:22:11,415 --> 00:22:16,295
- It's been a year.
- [sighs] Your little boy must be, what, six?

356
00:22:16,795 --> 00:22:19,172
- [sighs]
- And Evie, seven?

357
00:22:19,173 --> 00:22:20,674
No, eight.

358
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:24,344
They must love the idea
their daddy's James Bond.

359
00:22:24,970 --> 00:22:27,764
I understand why you don't want anyone
to know the truth.

360
00:22:27,848 --> 00:22:29,974
Is that what this is about?
Me lying to my family?

361
00:22:29,975 --> 00:22:32,311
You lied to the investigators first,
didn't you?

362
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:35,021
[sighs] I panicked.

363
00:22:35,022 --> 00:22:39,067
Said you didn't send the email,
even though it came under your login.

364
00:22:39,151 --> 00:22:40,360
[sighs]

365
00:22:41,069 --> 00:22:42,070
Do you want to read it?

366
00:22:43,322 --> 00:22:45,407
- Uh, not really.
- I think you should.

367
00:22:51,455 --> 00:22:54,124
"Anyone else surprised
by Tearney's outfit?

368
00:22:54,875 --> 00:22:56,709
ISIS chic." [chuckles]

369
00:22:56,710 --> 00:22:58,212
"Maybe she's undercover?"

370
00:22:58,754 --> 00:23:02,006
Uh, she wore a shawl
at a press conference.

371
00:23:02,007 --> 00:23:04,510
It... It... It looked a bit like... like...

372
00:23:05,969 --> 00:23:06,970
Mmm.

373
00:23:07,679 --> 00:23:14,352
You used a service email chain to imply that the head of MI5 was working undercover for a terrorist organization.

374
00:23:14,353 --> 00:23:15,979
But it was meant as a joke.

375
00:23:17,272 --> 00:23:20,275
But it's a pattern of behavior, Struan.

376
00:23:20,359 --> 00:23:22,027
Joking around.

377
00:23:22,945 --> 00:23:25,530
Undermining your superiors.

378
00:23:25,531 --> 00:23:28,867
Questioning the line of command.
Not taking your job seriously.

379
00:23:28,951 --> 00:23:31,828
And what we do here is very serious.

380
00:23:34,248 --> 00:23:38,585
So if you were to come back here
to work at the Park, I need to know that you have learnt your lesson.

381
00:23:39,127 --> 00:23:40,128
Absolutely!

382
00:23:40,796 --> 00:23:42,047
I can't promise anything.

383
00:23:44,716 --> 00:23:50,264
You probably know
how many people have made it back from Slough House to upstairs here at Regent's Park. Hmm?

384
00:23:50,889 --> 00:23:52,099
None.

385
00:23:53,392 --> 00:23:54,726
It's not impossible.

386
00:23:59,147 --> 00:24:03,068
Have you seen anything unusual
at Slough House, any activity?

387
00:24:09,491 --> 00:24:10,492
No.

388
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:14,705
[smacks lips] Uh...

389
00:24:17,708 --> 00:24:18,917
I don't think so.

390
00:24:23,380 --> 00:24:25,257
What sort of unusual activity?

391
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,344
It's a shame you haven't noticed anything.

392
00:24:29,428 --> 00:24:30,888
I was relying on you.

393
00:24:32,973 --> 00:24:34,474
You see, I have a problem.

394
00:24:35,434 --> 00:24:36,894
Quite a big problem.

395
00:24:37,686 --> 00:24:40,189
How would you like to be
part of the solution?

396
00:24:41,106 --> 00:24:43,066
[engine revving]

397
00:24:43,150 --> 00:24:44,026
[horn honking]

398
00:24:44,027 --> 00:24:46,277
[Roddy] Slow down! This isn't Mario Kart!

399
00:24:46,278 --> 00:24:48,321
Can you get Alan Black's
service record up on that?

400
00:24:48,322 --> 00:24:50,842
[scoffs] Can you stop wasting my time
with rhetorical questions?

401
00:24:50,866 --> 00:24:55,161
- [horn honking]
- [Roddy yelps] Can you just do it please? Or whatever the magic word is.

402
00:24:55,162 --> 00:24:57,580
How did you find me?
Those are the magic words.

403
00:24:57,581 --> 00:24:59,458
Stop dicking around, Roddy. Just do it.

404
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:02,585
No, but this is a major security breach.

405
00:25:02,586 --> 00:25:04,796
I need to review protocols
so it doesn't happen again.

406
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:07,632
You overlooked a massive weak spot
in your defenses.

407
00:25:07,633 --> 00:25:08,967
Impossible.

408
00:25:09,051 --> 00:25:11,136
I hacked the personnel database
at the Park.

409
00:25:11,220 --> 00:25:12,929
I-I changed my address.

410
00:25:12,930 --> 00:25:19,018
My phone, my Internet, my bills,
even my bank account are all linked to false IDs that rotate every 24 hours.

411
00:25:19,019 --> 00:25:21,438
I'm so far off the grid,
I don't even know where the grid is.

412
00:25:21,522 --> 00:25:22,523
Lamb followed you home.

413
00:25:24,525 --> 00:25:25,608
When the fuck?

414
00:25:25,609 --> 00:25:27,402
I don't know, but he told everyone.

415
00:25:29,613 --> 00:25:30,613
Black! Come on.

416
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:34,742
You worked with Black, didn't you?

417
00:25:34,743 --> 00:25:35,743
[typing]

418
00:25:35,786 --> 00:25:37,287
- Roddy!
- Yeah!

419
00:25:37,371 --> 00:25:39,914
What was Black doing in that house
with Hassan Ahmed?

420
00:25:39,915 --> 00:25:42,250
Any clues in anything he said or did?

421
00:25:42,251 --> 00:25:44,002
Yeah, on the last day he said, "Fuck you.

422
00:25:44,086 --> 00:25:46,648
I'm off to kidnap an Asian kid
and behead him for the Union Jack."

423
00:25:46,672 --> 00:25:48,757
Fuck's sake, Roddy. Right, fine. Okay?

424
00:25:49,675 --> 00:25:51,385
You drive like a maniac, you know.

425
00:25:51,927 --> 00:25:54,680
[tires squealing]

426
00:25:55,597 --> 00:25:57,766
- [River] That's him.
- [Roddy] Eyes on the road!

427
00:25:57,850 --> 00:25:58,850
Look ahead!

428
00:25:58,851 --> 00:26:01,144
I've definitely seen him somewhere.
Come on.

429
00:26:02,104 --> 00:26:05,231
We never crossed paths at Slough House.
I think he left before I joined the Park.

430
00:26:05,232 --> 00:26:07,192
This has literally nothing to do with me.

431
00:26:08,068 --> 00:26:09,528
[Diana] Do you recognize him?

432
00:26:10,404 --> 00:26:14,449
Alan Black.
Left Slough House soon after I arrived.

433
00:26:15,075 --> 00:26:16,285
Seen him since?

434
00:26:22,082 --> 00:26:23,083
You sure?

435
00:26:24,376 --> 00:26:27,421
You haven't seen him recently
in the company of Jackson Lamb?

436
00:26:30,424 --> 00:26:32,551
Uh, well, not since he left.

437
00:26:36,096 --> 00:26:37,181
[inhales sharply, sighs]

438
00:26:40,934 --> 00:26:43,186
Then you're not part
of the solution then, are you?

439
00:26:43,187 --> 00:26:44,979
You're just another problem.

440
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:47,232
[footsteps departing]

441
00:26:59,620 --> 00:27:02,163
What are you doing?
This isn't Blake's grave.

442
00:27:02,164 --> 00:27:03,665
I just need to know that she's okay.

443
00:27:03,749 --> 00:27:04,958
- All right?
- Why?

444
00:27:05,876 --> 00:27:07,336
She can't help you now!

445
00:27:08,045 --> 00:27:10,565
You'll be lucky if you get ten minutes
before the Park get here!

446
00:27:10,631 --> 00:27:12,966
I'll be out in five.
Just leave the engine running!

447
00:27:13,050 --> 00:27:14,051
Fuck.

448
00:27:31,485 --> 00:27:33,778
[voice mail] You have two new messages.

449
00:27:33,779 --> 00:27:39,075
- Message one.
- [beeps] This is Diana Taverner. You need to come to the Park straightaway.

450
00:27:39,076 --> 00:27:40,994
Jackson Lamb's gone rogue.

451
00:27:41,745 --> 00:27:47,459
- [voice mail] Message two.
- [beeps] Catherine, Diana Taverner again. I really need you to come to the Park.

452
00:27:47,543 --> 00:27:50,879
There are things
about Charles Partner's death that Lamb hasn't told you.

453
00:27:50,963 --> 00:27:52,172
Call me.

454
00:27:56,468 --> 00:27:57,677
[sighs]

455
00:27:57,678 --> 00:28:02,014
- [door opens]
- [keys jingling] [echoing] Morning.

456
00:28:05,769 --> 00:28:08,397
I picked up your blue suit.

457
00:28:10,899 --> 00:28:12,901
You could wear that today if you fancy.

458
00:28:15,696 --> 00:28:17,614
- Charles?
- [Jackson] What's taking so long?

459
00:28:18,824 --> 00:28:19,949
Get out of my bedroom.

460
00:28:19,950 --> 00:28:22,870
[stammers] What, you think I want
to catch you in your underwear?

461
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:29,042
- I imagine you'd like that.
- [scoffs] Almost as much as I'd like to see you in your nylon Y-fronts.

462
00:28:29,626 --> 00:28:30,919
Come on.

463
00:28:31,003 --> 00:28:32,045
Now!

464
00:28:32,129 --> 00:28:34,715
[footsteps departing]

465
00:28:41,555 --> 00:28:43,598
What was Taverner talking about?

466
00:28:43,599 --> 00:28:45,475
What don't I know about Charles's death?

467
00:28:45,559 --> 00:28:47,977
She's... [stammers]
screwing with your head.

468
00:28:47,978 --> 00:28:51,314
Look, you could leave with me now
or with less friendly people later.

469
00:28:51,315 --> 00:28:52,399
It's up to you.

470
00:28:53,358 --> 00:28:54,359
[sighs]

471
00:29:00,032 --> 00:29:01,908
No, leave... leave the phone.

472
00:29:01,909 --> 00:29:02,993
[sighs]

473
00:29:04,870 --> 00:29:06,079
[keys jingle]

474
00:29:15,005 --> 00:29:18,258
Hi. Sorry, can you, uh... Can you tell me
which room Sidonie Baker's in?

475
00:29:18,884 --> 00:29:20,301
It's immediate family only.

476
00:29:20,302 --> 00:29:21,845
Yeah, I'm her stepbrother.

477
00:29:21,929 --> 00:29:23,597
Can you sign in on the screen?

478
00:29:24,973 --> 00:29:25,974
Yeah, yeah.

479
00:29:29,102 --> 00:29:30,103
[clears throat]

480
00:29:36,860 --> 00:29:39,821
- Great. Which room?
- ICU room 4.

481
00:29:39,905 --> 00:29:42,065
- End of the corridor on the right.
- Great, thank you.

482
00:29:52,209 --> 00:29:53,335
Pierce?

483
00:29:56,672 --> 00:29:57,923
Baker has a visitor.

484
00:30:00,342 --> 00:30:02,219
[Pierce] What the fuck is he doing there?

485
00:30:02,719 --> 00:30:04,054
Who can get there fastest?

486
00:30:05,597 --> 00:30:08,308
[Pierce] Cartwright's back
at the hospital. Get him.

487
00:30:08,392 --> 00:30:09,434
With pleasure.

488
00:30:11,812 --> 00:30:13,730
[honking]

489
00:30:13,814 --> 00:30:15,107
Oh, do fuck off.

490
00:30:16,859 --> 00:30:18,610
It's River, isn't it?

491
00:30:18,694 --> 00:30:21,488
Has he gone off the rails,
and now we're paying the price?

492
00:30:21,572 --> 00:30:23,198
Well, not a million miles off.

493
00:30:23,949 --> 00:30:26,368
[sighs] Baker's been hurt. Moody's dead.

494
00:30:27,202 --> 00:30:29,537
- There's probably a C&amp;
- C out on all of us.

495
00:30:29,538 --> 00:30:30,789
Fuckers.

496
00:30:30,873 --> 00:30:32,624
How badly hurt is Sid?

497
00:30:32,708 --> 00:30:36,544
Uh, not as badly hurt as Moody's dead.
Did you catch that bit?

498
00:30:36,545 --> 00:30:40,757
Jed Moody was always going to end badly,
but I like Sid.

499
00:31:00,611 --> 00:31:04,281
[Jackson breathes deeply]

500
00:31:08,368 --> 00:31:09,369
Busy night?

501
00:31:09,453 --> 00:31:11,663
[sighs] You angling for overtime, Nick?

502
00:31:11,747 --> 00:31:14,749
- You're talking to the wrong bloke.
- Need to know if you're carrying a weapon.

503
00:31:14,750 --> 00:31:15,834
Nope.

504
00:31:15,918 --> 00:31:17,604
I'll have to check that.
Spread 'em, please.

505
00:31:17,628 --> 00:31:21,506
Please, Nick, shut the kid up.
Come on, it's embarrassing. You're a pro.

506
00:31:21,507 --> 00:31:24,092
You can tell from the fold of my clothes
I'm not carrying.

507
00:31:24,176 --> 00:31:29,848
- I'm afraid you don't get a choice...
- If he takes another step towards me, he'll be frisking me with broken wrists.

508
00:31:37,648 --> 00:31:38,649
Come on.

509
00:31:42,069 --> 00:31:44,404
[Jackson sighs]

510
00:31:49,618 --> 00:31:51,787
[Nick] Webb, you can drive.

511
00:31:52,371 --> 00:31:54,081
Ms. Standish, you're up front.

512
00:31:54,790 --> 00:31:57,000
Lamb, you're in the back with me.

513
00:31:59,086 --> 00:32:00,754
[Jackson sighs]

514
00:32:08,220 --> 00:32:09,221
Come on.

515
00:32:09,847 --> 00:32:11,682
[sucks teeth] Are you serious?

516
00:32:16,061 --> 00:32:17,771
[tires squealing]

517
00:32:22,192 --> 00:32:25,654
- Time's up, Cartwright. Screw all this.
- [Hobbs shouting, indistinct]

518
00:32:50,387 --> 00:32:51,387
[sighs]

519
00:32:51,388 --> 00:32:53,390
[rhythmic beeping]

520
00:33:00,772 --> 00:33:01,773
[sighs]

521
00:33:07,487 --> 00:33:08,530
[River] Come on.

522
00:33:08,614 --> 00:33:16,704
- Unbelievable.
- [chuckles] - You love it when I'm hard on you. - [scoffs, sniffles] [Sid] What about that story about you tailing Taverner?

523
00:33:16,705 --> 00:33:17,789
Is that just a myth?

524
00:33:20,918 --> 00:33:23,337
No. Not a myth, actually.
That really did happen.

525
00:33:25,297 --> 00:33:27,341
Shit.

526
00:33:31,512 --> 00:33:32,513
Thanks, Sid.

527
00:33:45,817 --> 00:33:47,152
Yeah, f...

528
00:33:47,236 --> 00:33:48,320
[sputtering] F...

529
00:34:07,548 --> 00:34:09,174
[panting]

530
00:34:21,478 --> 00:34:22,937
Wait, wait, wait!

531
00:34:22,938 --> 00:34:25,190
[panting]

532
00:34:25,274 --> 00:34:28,568
- [electronic voice] Door closing.
- Come on, come on, come on.

533
00:34:28,569 --> 00:34:29,610
[button clicking rapidly]

534
00:34:34,824 --> 00:34:37,494
- [Hobbs] For fuck...
- [panting] Hi.

535
00:34:39,621 --> 00:34:41,247
Routine or emergency?

536
00:34:41,248 --> 00:34:42,748
She's just switching wards.

537
00:34:42,833 --> 00:34:43,833
- Thank you.
- [thuds]

538
00:34:43,876 --> 00:34:44,960
[emergency bell rings]

539
00:34:47,629 --> 00:34:49,755
[alarm beeping]

540
00:35:00,058 --> 00:35:01,226
[panting]

541
00:35:03,312 --> 00:35:04,646
[River] Oi.

542
00:35:04,730 --> 00:35:06,481
- [grunts]
- [panting]

543
00:35:06,565 --> 00:35:07,858
[elevator bell dings]

544
00:35:12,321 --> 00:35:13,363
Hey!

545
00:35:17,576 --> 00:35:19,828
[panting]

546
00:35:22,247 --> 00:35:24,458
[sighs] Ah, shit.

547
00:35:37,429 --> 00:35:43,227
Right. About 20 miles outside of Harwich, we pass through some countryside.

548
00:35:43,727 --> 00:35:45,270
Looks like there's some woods.

549
00:35:46,522 --> 00:35:47,564
We leave him there, yeah?

550
00:35:48,607 --> 00:35:50,192
[Zeppo] That sounds good to me.

551
00:35:51,276 --> 00:35:52,277
Yeah?

552
00:35:52,819 --> 00:35:53,904
If you like.

553
00:35:58,242 --> 00:35:59,492
Do you hear that, kid?

554
00:35:59,493 --> 00:36:02,579
We're gonna leave you someplace
and someone is gonna find you, okay?

555
00:36:03,121 --> 00:36:04,998
Yeah? It's okay.

556
00:36:05,082 --> 00:36:07,644
Really, it's just a bit fucked up...
[chuckling] ...is what it is.

557
00:36:07,668 --> 00:36:09,043
[breathing heavily]

558
00:36:09,044 --> 00:36:12,589
We didn't mean it to go like this.
We just wanted to wake people up.

559
00:36:12,673 --> 00:36:14,841
Do you know what I mean?
It's... It is what it is.

560
00:36:14,842 --> 00:36:16,802
[breathing heavily] I'm, uh...

561
00:36:18,804 --> 00:36:19,972
I'm sorry.

562
00:36:26,728 --> 00:36:28,938
- You're sorry?
- Hey. Hey!

563
00:36:28,939 --> 00:36:31,065
Someone died, okay?

564
00:36:31,066 --> 00:36:33,193
Spook or not, that's not right.

565
00:36:33,277 --> 00:36:34,611
Are they sorry?

566
00:36:35,195 --> 00:36:37,698
When they kill our troops
and rape our women?

567
00:36:39,116 --> 00:36:40,117
Nah.

568
00:36:40,742 --> 00:36:41,869
Fuck that.

569
00:36:42,619 --> 00:36:43,620
"Sorry"?

570
00:36:44,454 --> 00:36:47,415
- What the fuck is wrong with you, mate?
- [chuckles] What's... What's wro...

571
00:36:47,416 --> 00:36:51,002
The kid is not a murderer, okay?
And neither am I.

572
00:36:51,003 --> 00:36:52,379
I am though, aren't I?

573
00:36:53,839 --> 00:36:57,301
The way I see it, I'm already going down
for one murder, so what's a second?

574
00:36:59,219 --> 00:37:00,595
Fuck it.

575
00:37:00,596 --> 00:37:02,824
- We're killing him.
- [Larry] I'm not killing anyone, mate.

576
00:37:02,848 --> 00:37:04,557
- [Larry] We've lost our fucking...
- [Zeppo] Take it easy!

577
00:37:04,558 --> 00:37:10,147
[Curly] Shut your mouths!
The question is then whether you've got the balls to stop me, isn't it?

578
00:37:12,274 --> 00:37:13,275
Yes?

579
00:37:20,407 --> 00:37:22,618
[Struan breathing heavily]

580
00:37:25,621 --> 00:37:26,705
[cell phone buzzing]

581
00:37:27,664 --> 00:37:28,874
[Struan sighs]

582
00:37:32,461 --> 00:37:35,214
- Yeah?
- Inbound with Lamb and Standish.

583
00:37:35,839 --> 00:37:38,967
[Jackson] Tell her she best interrogate me
in a room with a window.

584
00:37:39,635 --> 00:37:43,222
I had a lamb bhuna earlier
that's gonna make its presence felt.

585
00:37:45,349 --> 00:37:47,851
[locks clicking]

586
00:37:51,396 --> 00:37:52,480
What's happening?

587
00:37:52,481 --> 00:37:54,775
Catherine Standish is being brought in.

588
00:37:55,400 --> 00:37:58,194
I'm sure I can make her remember
what you seem to have forgotten.

589
00:37:58,195 --> 00:37:59,696
What happens to me?

590
00:37:59,780 --> 00:38:01,656
Are you gonna tell my wife
I don't work here?

591
00:38:01,657 --> 00:38:05,952
Yes. And I'm gonna tell her
you're being held as part of the investigation into Alan Black's death.

592
00:38:05,953 --> 00:38:08,288
No! No, wait, wait, no, no.
Please, please, please.

593
00:38:08,872 --> 00:38:10,206
It's coming back to me now.

594
00:38:10,207 --> 00:38:13,418
I... I blanked it out because it felt like
something I shouldn't have seen.

595
00:38:14,545 --> 00:38:21,760
I definitely remember seeing Lamb
and Alan Black together after Black had left Slough House.

596
00:38:25,514 --> 00:38:28,642
I-If I rack my brains,
I... I can probably put a date on it.

597
00:38:37,150 --> 00:38:39,110
[inhales sharply]
Well, we've got it on tape.

598
00:38:39,111 --> 00:38:42,406
Let's err on the side of caution.
Get it down in writing.

599
00:38:45,033 --> 00:38:46,034
Sit.

600
00:38:46,660 --> 00:38:47,660
[sneezes]

601
00:38:47,661 --> 00:38:49,580
[grunting, sniffling]

602
00:38:52,624 --> 00:38:55,210
Is she gonna stick us
in those new basement cells?

603
00:38:55,752 --> 00:38:57,671
I-I... I've not seen them myself.

604
00:38:58,422 --> 00:39:00,424
I used to work out of the old building.

605
00:39:02,050 --> 00:39:07,472
But, you know... [sighs]
I... I've been in the Stasi cells, so anything you've got will be a luxury.

606
00:39:08,390 --> 00:39:10,517
[sniffles] And then what?

607
00:39:10,601 --> 00:39:16,940
Lady Di's gonna rewrite the timeline, stick Slough House in the frame for this fucking disaster.

608
00:39:20,736 --> 00:39:22,695
[sneezes, groans]

609
00:39:22,696 --> 00:39:23,780
[sniffles]

610
00:39:24,781 --> 00:39:26,325
Is no one gonna say "Bless you"?

611
00:39:27,576 --> 00:39:28,577
No?

612
00:39:29,578 --> 00:39:31,205
Bit rude. [sniffs]

613
00:39:32,623 --> 00:39:37,211
[sighs] Course, she'd rather
that kid had his head cut off than admit it was her fault.

614
00:39:38,629 --> 00:39:40,464
She's scorching the earth.

615
00:39:41,215 --> 00:39:42,841
She's covering her tracks.

616
00:39:43,884 --> 00:39:47,971
But it's the covering of the tracks
that always gets you in the end, isn't that right, Nick?

617
00:39:49,306 --> 00:39:51,058
I mean, she knows that, of course.

618
00:39:52,017 --> 00:39:54,019
She thinks she's the exception.

619
00:39:55,604 --> 00:39:57,439
That's what everybody thinks.

620
00:39:57,523 --> 00:39:58,857
Everybody's always wrong.

621
00:39:58,941 --> 00:40:02,277
Look, the last time I was in the Park,
Diana Taverner was in charge.

622
00:40:02,361 --> 00:40:05,280
Until that changes, I'll do what she says.

623
00:40:05,364 --> 00:40:07,282
Yeah, but it's all gonna unravel, Nick.

624
00:40:07,366 --> 00:40:15,123
The sensible thing to do would be
forget Lady Di's London rules and concentrate on finding that kid before he gets whacked.

625
00:40:15,207 --> 00:40:17,959
[sniffles] If that's not already happened.

626
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,044
[sneezes]

627
00:40:19,628 --> 00:40:23,214
Oh, Jesus! You keep a cat in here or what?

628
00:40:23,215 --> 00:40:26,676
[sniffles, groans]
Standish, you got a tissue in that bag?

629
00:40:26,677 --> 00:40:27,677
[sniffles]

630
00:40:31,723 --> 00:40:33,350
I've only got one left.

631
00:40:34,351 --> 00:40:35,560
Give us it here then.

632
00:40:35,561 --> 00:40:38,396
I have a question I want answered first.

633
00:40:38,397 --> 00:40:40,315
[sighs] Oh, for... What now?

634
00:40:40,399 --> 00:40:44,986
The question pertains to something that was raised in a voice mail that I received tonight.

635
00:40:44,987 --> 00:40:47,614
[sighs] I'll tell you later.

636
00:40:48,866 --> 00:40:49,867
Pinkie promise.

637
00:40:51,743 --> 00:40:52,828
Tissue.

638
00:40:58,041 --> 00:41:00,710
Now, we all know I'm not
going to shoot you dead, Mr. Webb.

639
00:41:00,711 --> 00:41:03,255
But I'll put a bullet through your foot
if I have to.

640
00:41:04,131 --> 00:41:05,131
Pull over.

641
00:41:07,134 --> 00:41:09,428
- I said pull over.
- Yeah, all right, all right.

642
00:41:12,890 --> 00:41:14,892
[Jackson] This is your stop, boys.

643
00:41:22,524 --> 00:41:25,152
You two can walk from here
if that's all right.

644
00:41:43,670 --> 00:41:46,590
You're full of surprises, Standish.
You know that?

645
00:41:49,593 --> 00:41:52,179
How'd you know my Y-fronts are nylon?

646
00:41:53,430 --> 00:41:55,098
Because I have to buy them for you.

647
00:41:56,767 --> 00:41:57,809
Drip-dry.

648
00:41:58,560 --> 00:41:59,561
Very efficient.

649
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:19,331
[sobbing, muffled]
